\title{Hausdorff space (point-set)}
\date{2023-09-15}
\taxon{definition}
\author{James R. Munkres}

\def\opens[X]{\mathcal{O}(\X)}

\p{
  A space #{X} is called \em{Hausdorff} if for any two distinct points #{x_1,
  x_2 \in X}, there exist a \em{disjoint} pair of open neighbourhoods #{U_1, U_2
  \in \opens{X}}, of #{x_1} and #{x_2}.
}

\p{
  Adapted from [Topology by Munkres](munkres-topology-2000).
}
